For a long time, valvettiturai, used represent a small coastal village on the northeast coast of the Jaffna Peninsula in Sri Lanka's north which was approximately 300 hectares in size which is also called as Valvai.now it includes few neighboring villages and called as valvettiturai Pattinam (City).  It is pronounced as Valvettithurai (val-vet-ti-thu-rai). 


The history of this beautiful village starts as early as A.C 150, the famous poem wrritten during this period ‘Pattinapalai’ by Uthirakannar, on 29th and 30th lines, he says as they brought food to kaveri (a city in INDIA) from valai.


Valvettithurai city has a remarkable place in history because It was here the LTTE leader Velupillai Prabhakaran was born.